1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:03,500
Your Bitcoin is sitting idle.
What if it could generate yield every single week?

2
00:00:03,500 --> 00:00:07,500
Introducing sBTC Options Vault —
the first covered call options platform

3
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:12,000
built on Bitcoin, powered by Stacks.

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Here's how it works.
An option is a contract between two parties.

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:19,500
The buyer pays a small premium —
say 0.05 sBTC —

6
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:23,500
for the right to profit if Bitcoin's price
rises above a set strike price before expiry.

7
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:26,000
The risk? Only the premium you paid.

8
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,000
The reward? Potentially massive upside.

9
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,500
Getting started is simple.
Connect your Leather or Xverse wallet,

10
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:37,000
and you'll instantly see the vault dashboard —
total value locked,

11
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,500
current share price, and the active epoch.

12
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:45,000
Everything updates in real-time
from on-chain data.

13
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,500
Head to the Market page
to browse available options.

14
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:52,500
Each listing shows the strike price,
premium cost, and collateral backing.

15
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:55,000
Found one you like?
Click "Buy Option,"

16
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,500
confirm the transaction in your wallet,
and your premium flows directly

17
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:02,000
into the vault through
the Stacks blockchain.

18
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:06,500
Your position is now live —
fully on-chain, fully transparent.

19
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:10,000
Once you've bought an option,
track it in real-time.

20
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:14,500
The system pulls live Bitcoin prices
from the on-chain oracle

21
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:17,500
and calculates your profit
and loss instantly.

22
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:21,000
Green means you're "In the Money" —
Bitcoin is above your strike

23
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,000
and you're in profit.

24
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,500
Orange means "Out of the Money" —

25
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:29,000
but remember, your maximum loss
is always capped at the premium you paid.

26
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Here's where it gets exciting.

27
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,500
When Bitcoin settles above your strike price,
you're in the money.

28
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:38,500
The payout formula is simple:
collateral times the price difference,

29
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:41,000
divided by the settlement price.

30
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:44,500
In this example — with a strike of $90,000
and settlement at $100,000 —

31
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:48,500
your 0.05 sBTC premium
turns into 0.50 sBTC.

32
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:52,000
That's a 900% return on your investment.

33
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:55,000
And if Bitcoin stays below the strike?

34
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,500
Your option simply expires.
You lose only the premium —

35
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:00,000
0.05 sBTC. That's it.

36
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Unlike leveraged trading
where you can get liquidated,

37
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,500
with options your downside
is always defined and limited.

38
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:10,000
You know your maximum risk
before you even enter the trade.

39
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,500
Ready to profit?
Claim your payout with one click

40
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:16,000
and it flows straight to your wallet.

41
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:20,000
sBTC Options Vault —
structured yield on Bitcoin,

42
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:24,000
fully on-chain, fully transparent.
Start trading now.
